00:20:14,360 --> 00:20:15,881
where we conducted the community survey,

416
00:20:16,141 --> 00:20:18,001
we received a considerable number of complaints

417
00:20:18,021 --> 00:20:19,962
from players who felt as though regardless

418
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:21,482
of the intention of the survey,

419
00:20:21,842 --> 00:20:23,623
it was too late for us to redeem ourselves.

420
00:20:24,663 --> 00:20:26,884
Our response was as follows, and I'm paraphrasing

421
00:20:26,944 --> 00:20:28,625
as you can see a very long admin post.

422
00:20:30,305 --> 00:20:32,406
It's difficult to help a community that's so negative.

423
00:20:33,347 --> 00:20:36,710
The purpose of the survey was to give a voice to players who feel uncomfortable posting in the

424
00:20:36,730 --> 00:20:42,154
forums, because of the negativity, and being mean doesn't open dialogue for proactive solutions.

425
00:20:43,836 --> 00:20:47,979
Even following that initial post, players continued to harass us, saying that we didn't

426
00:20:47,999 --> 00:20:51,862
care about our community and that the requests for new features had gone unnoticed for quite

427
00:20:51,902 --> 00:20:57,266
some time. Aha! This provided an opportunity for us to be more transparent to our user base.

428
00:20:58,252 --> 00:21:01,694
We went on to describe a bit more about the way new features are worked on and how they

429
00:21:01,714 --> 00:21:04,436
get through a suggestion pipeline and eventually deployed by our devs.

430
00:21:05,157 --> 00:21:09,640
It also gave us a chance to explain to players that the voice of so few in the forum doesn't

431
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:11,982
always represent the best interest of the entire community.

432
00:21:12,262 --> 00:21:15,404
I think that was noted in the first talk this morning for the community summit, which it's

433
00:21:15,564 --> 00:21:21,529
roughly 1 in 1,000 that actually respond in the forums, so it's such a small, small number

434
00:21:21,549 --> 00:21:24,211
of players, but they can also be some of the worst players.

435
00:21:27,246 --> 00:21:28,667
And after a bit of explanation,

436
00:21:28,968 --> 00:21:31,390
players received the response very positively.

437
00:21:32,350 --> 00:21:34,092
This player is thanking us for taking the time

438
00:21:34,132 --> 00:21:35,073
to address their concerns,

439
00:21:35,393 --> 00:21:37,395
and admitted that they had lost faith in our ability

440
00:21:37,415 --> 00:21:38,536
to provide customer service,

441
00:21:38,816 --> 00:21:40,257
simply because we weren't being as honest

442
00:21:40,297 --> 00:21:40,978
as we should have been.

443
00:21:43,020 --> 00:21:45,062
This player's feedback was actually very well put,

444
00:21:45,542 --> 00:21:46,803
saying that despite their comments,

445
00:21:47,023 --> 00:21:49,245
they were only interested in engaging in a dialogue,

446
00:21:49,345 --> 00:21:51,507
and didn't realize that we would have taken it

447
00:21:51,567 --> 00:21:52,568
as seriously as we did.

448
00:21:54,988 --> 00:21:58,870
Another player saying that our intent interactions in the forums turned them from the grumpiest

449
00:21:58,930 --> 00:22:05,114
player to the most content. And a player telling us that we just provided them with the best

450
00:22:05,214 --> 00:22:11,357
in-game customer service and feedback that they've ever received. This player is noting

451
00:22:11,397 --> 00:22:16,039
that baby steps helped the situation and actually provided useful information, encouraging us

452
00:22:16,059 --> 00:22:17,220
to be as honest as possible.

