00:22:27,198 --> 00:22:28,559
And this screenshot goes a long way

457
00:22:28,619 --> 00:22:30,420
in illustrating just how frustrating it can be

458
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:31,501
to be a community manager.

459
00:22:32,062 --> 00:22:34,363
Players assault you with abuse and harassment

460
00:22:34,604 --> 00:22:36,025
and expect you to wait around for praise

461
00:22:36,105 --> 00:22:37,986
once you've managed to push through to a breakthrough.

462
00:22:38,567 --> 00:22:40,228
It's exhausting and draining,

463
00:22:40,528 --> 00:22:42,149
and yet we encounter it every single day.

464
00:22:44,531 --> 00:22:45,832
So what does this adoration mean?

465
00:22:47,197 --> 00:22:52,721
In this first graph, the bump that you see here in August is a 67% increase in revenue

466
00:22:52,761 --> 00:22:56,624
week over week following our interactions we had with our villains players in the forums

467
00:22:56,724 --> 00:22:58,085
in regards to the community survey.

468
00:22:58,965 --> 00:23:02,748
The long draining afternoon of abuse actually provided worthwhile results.

469
00:23:05,081 --> 00:23:06,622
The second graph I have here is following

